-- Getting Gazebo simulations to run --
0. Install Ubuntu 18.04 or derivative of it
1. Install ROS Melodic Morenia and Gazebo9
2. Make sure you have the "ros-melodic-gazebo-ros-pkgs" package
3. Build the packages in the workspace
4. Start simulation by running "./sim.sh"

Step by step commands:

```
# Add ROS repository
sudo sh -c 'echo "deb http://packages.ros.org/ros/ubuntu $(lsb_release -sc) main" > /etc/apt/sources.list.d/ros-latest.list'
sudo apt-key adv --keyserver hkp://ha.pool.sks-keyservers.net:80 --recv-key 421C365BD9FF1F717815A3895523BAEEB01FA116

# With this mirror we get newest Gazebo 9.x instead of 9.0.
sudo sh -c 'echo "deb http://packages.osrfoundation.org/gazebo/ubuntu-stable `lsb_release -cs` main" > /etc/apt/sources.list.d/gazebo-stable.list'
wget http://packages.osrfoundation.org/gazebo.key -O - | sudo apt-key add -

# Install ROS and Gazebo
sudo apt-get update
sudo apt-get install -y ros-melodic-desktop-full gazebo9 ros-melodic-gazebo-ros-pkgs ros-melodic-rqt-multiplot ros-melodic-velodyne-simulator
sudo apt-get upgrade libignition-math2

source /opt/ros/melodic/setup.bash

# Clone the repository
git clone https://bitbucket.org/dtucar/autonomous-ecocar.git

# Compile the code
cd autonomous-ecocar/catkin_ws_sim/
catkin_make

# Start the simulation script
# It starts rqt with the simulation plugin
./sim.sh
```
